(148, '2012-07-31 23:29:39', 1, 597, 'Princewill', 'info@ars-fine.com', 'why does vista uses virtual memroy first then ram??!!?I run Vista Business 32bit with 4gigs of ram in my laptop.Im a heavy multi tasker so i run a lot of programs the same time,-firefox with 10-20 tabs with a lot of flash websites-google chrome with 8-12 tabs with a lot of flash websites-4 instances of explorer windows-4 instances of notepad-flashget-Limewire 5 pro-yahoo messenger 10-windows live messenger-dap-win defender-norton 360 v2-cam frog-skype-HWmonitor from CPU-ID-memroy turbo (i use it for memroy usage monitor)-coretemp (cpu temp monitor)-taskmanager (used for cpu usage monitor).And that is always my setup whenever i use my laptop.The annoying thing is, sometimes vista keeps popping up a message box telling me that my computer is low in memroy, even though i have 700megs free or RAM (even when checking in taks manager it read 700mb free).after increasing the pagefile to 4gigs, vista now neglects to use 1.2gigs of RAM during idle (what a waste!). then if my free RAM starts to drop to the 700megs line then vista starts to complain about low memroy again!And my HDD is always active and sometimes slows my computer to a crawl for 10-20 secs becuase of the 100% usage of HDD cranking and exchanging data. While i still have 700megs of free RAM! Damn!I tried disabling the pagefile, and vista managed to leave 400megs of unused ram before it starts to freak out that memroy is low. Plus, i always had my apps crashing on me (firefox and chrome even sometimes stops a script due to low memroy conditions). Vista is denying my apps of memroy causing them to crash while there is still 400megs of free RAM! That is just stupid!For what is it saving the 400 megs for? If evidently i need it!How can i stop vista from using the virtual memroy first and then neglects to use the much faster RAM.Its counter intuitive to use the HDD first for memroy then RAM. That is really stupid. Then it leaves 700megs just sitting there unused while vista screams LOW MEMORY!!!My memroy modules are fine and i always check them using vista\'s recovery disc memroy diagnostics tool every month.Has anyone know a fix?like a registry modification?Or even a hack?Its really annoying vista doing this. it bugs me out!'),
